author: Kaelan Deese
title: New Jersey reports nearly 2,500 new coronavirus cases in one day
description: New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy (D) announced a total of more 6,800 cases of COVID-19 in the state on Thursday, marking an uptick of 2,492 cases since Wednesday.
content:
New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy (D) announced a total of more 6,800 cases of COVID-19 in the state on Thursday, marking an uptick of 2,492 cases since Wednesday.
